				<h2>IR distance sensor</h2>
<p>I am trying to make a IR distance sensor. I have seen <a href="http://www.instructables.com/id/Simple-IR-proximity-sensor-with-Arduino/" rel="nofollow">this</a> online. My goal however is to see the distance between a IR transmitter and my IR sensor. In the example above he uses the IR led's ambient light and timing to track the distance. Is there a way to find the distance between lets say a IR remote and a sensor? It would only have to be accurate to about 1 meter. I am also open to other ideas of accurately tracking distance between two objects weither that be bluetooth/ir/ultrasonic </p>

