				<p><p>You would be better off setting up something that uses a stereoscopic technique. Think of something like <a href="http://www.tobii.com/xperience/products/" rel="nofollow" title="the Tobii EyeX">this</a>. Another similar product is the Leap Motion.</p>

<p>In your case, you could probably get away with just two IR sensors, and one emitter, because of your setup. However, "accurate to 1 meter" is not realistic for most kinds of IR rigs. They usually only function <em>within</em> 0.5 meters, but can be pretty accurate when tracking something inside of their range.</p>
